Package com.github.yellowstonegames.core

Class Maker

java.lang.Object
com.github.yellowstonegames.core.Maker
public class Maker
extends java.lang.Object
Utility methods for more easily constructing data structures, particularly those in jdkgdxds. All static methods; meant to be imported with import static squidpony.Maker.*. Constructing generic-typed maps here is not type-safe.

    • orderedMap

      public static <K,​ V> com.github.tommyettinger.ds.ObjectObjectOrderedMap<K,​V> orderedMap​(K k0, V v0, java.lang.Object... rest)
      Makes an ObjectObjectOrderedMap with key and value types inferred from the types of k0 and v0, and considers all parameters key-value pairs, casting the Objects at positions 0, 2, 4... etc. to K and the objects at positions 1, 3, 5... etc. to V. If rest has an odd-number length, then it discards the last item. If any pair of items in rest cannot be cast to the correct type of K or V, then this inserts nothing for that pair. You can pass an array containing keys and values for rest, but k0 and v0 can't be inside that array.
      Type Parameters:
      K - the type of keys in the returned ObjectObjectOrderedMap; if not specified, will be inferred from k0
      V - the type of values in the returned ObjectObjectOrderedMap; if not specified, will be inferred from v0
      Parameters:
      k0 - the first key; used to infer the types of other keys if generic parameters aren't specified.
      v0 - the first value; used to infer the types of other values if generic parameters aren't specified.
      rest - an array or vararg of keys and values in pairs; should contain alternating K, V, K, V... elements
      Returns:
      a freshly-made ObjectObjectOrderedMap with K keys and V values, using k0, v0, and the contents of rest to fill it

    • orderedMap

      public static <K,​ V> com.github.tommyettinger.ds.ObjectObjectOrderedMap<K,​V> orderedMap()
      Makes an empty ObjectObjectOrderedMap; needs key and value types to be specified in order to work. For an empty ObjectObjectOrderedMap with String keys and Coord values, you could use Maker.<String, Coord>orderedMap();. Using the new keyword is probably just as easy in this case; this method is provided for completeness relative to orderedMap() with 2 or more parameters.
      Type Parameters:
      K - the type of keys in the returned ObjectObjectOrderedMap; cannot be inferred and must be specified
      V - the type of values in the returned ObjectObjectOrderedMap; cannot be inferred and must be specified
      Returns:
      an empty ObjectObjectOrderedMap with the given key and value types.

    • caseInsensitiveOrderedMap

      public static <V> com.github.tommyettinger.ds.CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap<V> caseInsensitiveOrderedMap​(java.lang.CharSequence k0, V v0, java.lang.Object... rest)
      Makes an CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap with the value type inferred from the type of v0, and considers all parameters key-value pairs, casting the Objects at positions 0, 2, 4... etc. to CharSequence and the objects at positions 1, 3, 5... etc. to V. If rest has an odd-number length, then it discards the last item. If any pair of items in rest cannot be cast to the correct type of CharSequence or V (such as if the key is null), then this inserts nothing for that pair. You can pass an array containing keys and values for rest, but k0 and v0 can't be inside that array.
      Type Parameters:
      V - the type of values in the returned CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap; if not specified, will be inferred from v0
      Parameters:
      k0 - the first key; this can be any implementation of CharSequence, and is typically a String
      v0 - the first value; used to infer the types of other values if generic parameters aren't specified
      rest - an array or vararg of keys and values in pairs; should contain alternating CharSequence, V, CharSequence, V... elements
      Returns:
      a freshly-made CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap with V values, using k0, v0, and the contents of rest to fill it

    • caseInsensitiveOrderedMap

      public static <V> com.github.tommyettinger.ds.CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap<V> caseInsensitiveOrderedMap()
      Makes an empty CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap; needs the value type to be specified in order to work. For an empty CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap with Coord values, you could use Maker.<Coord>orderedMap();. Using the new keyword is probably just as easy in this case; this method is provided for completeness relative to caseInsensitiveOrderedMap() with 2 or more parameters.
      Type Parameters:
      V - the type of values in the returned CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap; cannot be inferred and must be specified
      Returns:
      an empty CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap with the given key and value types.
